               <p>JAMES RIGBY. I am a <rs id="t18260622-74-viclabel353" type="occupation">watchmaker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260622-74-victim518 t18260622-74-viclabel353"></join>, and live at Charing-cross. On the 17th of May, about four or five o'clock, I was in <placeName id="t18260622-74-crimeloc354">Red-lion-street, Holborn</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18260622-74-crimeloc354" type="placeName" value="Red-lion-street, Holborn"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18260622-74-crimeloc354" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260622-74-off351 t18260622-74-crimeloc354"></join>; I felt something twitch at my coat pocket; I disengaged myself from a gentleman I was walking with, and looked for some person runing, but I saw no one; I then saw the prisoner looking through a shop window - I collared him, threw open his coat, and found my handkerchief under his arm, covered with his coat - I knocked him down, and intended nothing further, but he fell into the hands of the street-keeper.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260622-74-person519">
                  WILLIAM 
                  PACEY
               <interp inst="t18260622-74-person519" type="surname" value="PACEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260622-74-person519" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260622-74-person519" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was walking with Mr. Rigby, and he felt something at his pocket; the prisoner was looking in at a window - Mr. Rigby took hold of him, and took this handkerchief from under his coat.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260622-74-person520">
                  MATTHIAS 
                  WELDHEN
               <interp inst="t18260622-74-person520" type="surname" value="WELDHEN"></interp>
